						               													<description>From the back of the book;&amp;#10;Introduction to Star Fleet Battles is a complete game, but is also the gateway to all the excitement which is Game: Star Fleet Battles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;User Description&amp;#10;The aim of this book is to introduce a new player to the complex game system of Game: Star Fleet Battles, but it can be used as a complete game in itself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It takes the reader slowly through the rules by small scenarios and adding more rules to the game in each scenario played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played on a fold-out A1 hex map with die-cut playing starship pieces.  Each scenario has its own goal for each player to win the game.  The scenarios in the book start off with solo player games like piloting a starship through an asteroid belt, then later with two-player battle game scenarios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Included with Introduction to Star Fleet Battles;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Step-by-Step Instructions.&amp;#10;     54 Die-Cut Playing Pieces.&amp;#10;     Game Map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Re-implemented by Star Fleet Battles Cadet Training Manual&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
